The paper deals with the properties of loss surfaces of deep neural networks, which are primarily studied in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the universal approximation capabilities of neural networks (cs.NE), and the transferability of patterns across datasets (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper touches upon the concept of smoothness in patterns, which is relevant to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and the analysis of neural networks (cs.IT).
